1
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:25,440
My dad doesn't approve of me
playing music.

2
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:29,400
If he knew I had a band,
he would beat me for sure.

3
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:31,040
<i>With the Honor Student Award,</i>

4
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:33,680
<i>do you wish for any gifts</i>
<i>from your parents?</i>

5
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:35,240
A new piano?

6
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:37,600
PREVIOUSLY

7
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:39,160
<i>This one caused trouble.</i>

8
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:43,000
Find me

9
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:44,760
100,000 baht.

10
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:46,600
You used to be a musician.

11
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:48,080
<i>You used to play guitar too.</i>

12
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:51,080
If you don't quit music,
you are no longer my son!

13
00:03:51,160 --> 00:03:53,200
Please take your time.

14
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:55,920
These pianos
all meet professional standards.

15
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:58,480
<i>If only I could make a wish,</i>

16
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:02,080
<i>I would wish for someone</i>
<i>who truly understands me.</i>

17
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:14,120
I hope you don't mind that I join you.

18
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:19,680
Wait.

19
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,360
I don't think we've met before.

20
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:29,720
You're right.

21
00:06:30,880 --> 00:06:34,560
I saw you playing the piano
and I couldn't help it.

22
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:39,040
I guess you flunked a test
or got ditched by some dude.

23
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:42,280
That's why you were
so aggressive with the piano.

24
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:45,360
How I play the piano
is none of your business.

25
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:48,120
Music is not an emotional punching bag.

26
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:51,400
If you have problems,

27
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:53,320
you probably have to face them

28
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:57,000
instead of taking it out on the piano.

29
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:03,600
I think you got me wrong.

30
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:06,880
My life is good.

31
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,800
I got the top score in every semester.

32
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:12,680
I am the champion of the piano contest.

33
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:14,960
My family is wealthy.

34
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:18,040
My parents provide everything for me.

35
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:21,000
You know what?

36
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:23,520
Even for toys,

37
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:26,720
I don't have to bother
choosing them myself.

38
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:33,560
I see.

39
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:38,920
A life with no freedom…

40
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,520
is no different from a walking doll.

41
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:52,920
Hey.

42
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:55,040
Don't cry.

43
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:01,640
Well,

44
00:08:02,280 --> 00:08:04,320
would you like me to play guitar for you?

45
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:11,560
What do you say?
That might help you stop crying.

46
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:16,760
Wait here.

47
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:27,080
In many parts of your life,
you might have no choice.

48
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:29,200
But in this moment,

49
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:31,280
you can make the choice.

50
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:34,520
I'll play any song you pick.

51
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:36,880
Here.

52
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:00,440
I want this one.

53
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:03,160
The song title hit my heart already.

54
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,080
Let me see.

55
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:14,080
"Out of Reach."

56
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:16,560
OUT OF REACH

57
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:30,160
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

58
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:36,560
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

59
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:43,160
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

60
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:48,400
<i>But never reaching you</i>

61
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:54,280
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

62
00:09:55,720 --> 00:10:00,640
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

63
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:07,320
<i>I'm just an ordinary man</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

64
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:13,160
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

65
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:18,760
<i>You are out of reach</i>

66
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:25,080
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

67
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:31,320
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

68
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:36,640
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

69
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:42,400
<i>How much longer can I bear this pain?</i>

70
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:48,200
<i>How much longer must I wait in vain?</i>

71
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:54,920
<i>I really don't know what move to make</i>

72
00:10:55,720 --> 00:11:00,880
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

73
00:11:08,760 --> 00:11:10,680
Here's your delivery note.

74
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:13,120
We will transport the piano
to your place tomorrow.

75
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:14,720
Thank you.

76
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:24,760
You've made the right choice.

77
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:30,800
This piano

78
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:32,480
has a beautiful tone.

79
00:11:34,920 --> 00:11:37,000
Thanks to your guitar.

80
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:39,600
It helped me make a decision.

81
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:42,440
And on top of that…

82
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:47,320
What?

83
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:50,000
I just experienced

84
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:52,720
playing piano with pure joy

85
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:54,520
for the first time.

86
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:08,600
PETCH PANJIN

87
00:12:09,920 --> 00:12:10,880
Done.

88
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:14,560
Nice to meet you, Petch.

89
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:16,800
Same here.

90
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:19,800
You can text me anytime.

91
00:12:21,040 --> 00:12:22,000
Natedao.

92
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:27,920
My friend is waiting for me.

93
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:28,960
Later, then.

94
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:31,640
My driver will pick me up.

95
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:32,920
Do you need a ride?

96
00:12:34,640 --> 00:12:35,600
It's okay.

97
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:37,960
I'll take the bus.
It's only one stop from here.

98
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:49,400
Miss.

99
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:53,160
I've finished with the insurance agent.
Please wait for about 20 minutes.

100
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:55,880
Oh, that's all right.

101
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:59,560
You don't have to come pick me up.
I'll go home by myself.

102
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:00,760
<i>All right, miss.</i>

103
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:10,280
Petch.

104
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:12,760
Hey.

105
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:15,960
Where's your driver then?

106
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:18,480
I changed my mind.

107
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:20,720
I think I'll try
taking the bus home today.

108
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:23,640
Which number do I have to take?

109
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:30,200
This one. Follow me.

110
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:16,720
Hold onto this.

111
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:26,160
It's crowded in here.

112
00:14:27,520 --> 00:14:29,160
Usual for buses.

113
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:30,600
Fares, please.

114
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:33,040
Fares, please.

115
00:14:33,560 --> 00:14:35,120
- How much is it?
- Two people, please.

116
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:46,600
Can I keep the tickets?

117
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,160
Why?

118
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:51,040
Just hand it to me.

119
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:11,640
<i>Sorry, the number you have dialed</i>
<i>is not available at the moment.</i>

120
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:13,000
Anything?

121
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:15,040
Dao turned off her phone.

122
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:16,560
I couldn't reach her.

123
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:08,600
We can't count on you.

124
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:10,920
How could you let Dao
go back home on her own?

125
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:11,880
Apologies, ma'am.

126
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:13,960
I don't want to hear a word.

127
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:17,120
If anything happens to Dao,
I won't be easy on you.

128
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:19,320
Go! Get lost!

129
00:16:22,520 --> 00:16:24,120
Ake, where are you going?

130
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:27,080
I sent a message to my men.
They can help find Dao.

131
00:16:27,680 --> 00:16:30,240
I'll check at her friends' houses.

132
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:32,200
I'll go with you.

133
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:33,440
It's all right.

134
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:35,160
I will take care of it.

135
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:38,200
I guarantee you that we will find Dao
by the end of the day.

136
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:42,720
Wow, Dao.

137
00:16:43,320 --> 00:16:44,360
Is this your place?

138
00:16:45,760 --> 00:16:46,600
Yes.

139
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:49,280
It's as big as a palace.

140
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:51,160
It's huge,

141
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:53,760
but I feel so alone.

142
00:16:56,320 --> 00:16:58,760
Come on, don't say that.

143
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:02,320
I know.

144
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:07,520
It's time to get back to reality.

145
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:24,079
Later, then.

146
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:25,160
Dao!

147
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:29,520
How did that punk tag along?

148
00:17:30,560 --> 00:17:31,480
Ake.

149
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:33,440
Careful how you speak to him.

150
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:35,080
He's my friend.

151
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:36,880
Dao.

152
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:38,840
How could you call that punk a friend?

153
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:40,760
- Ake!
- You.

154
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:43,320
Better know your place.

155
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:47,280
Dao is out of your league.

156
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:49,280
Get lost.

157
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:51,040
You absolute mongrel.

158
00:17:51,120 --> 00:17:53,240
Where did you learn
the mongrel language then?

159
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:55,960
Or you're a mongrel like me.

160
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:00,360
How dare you?

161
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:02,680
You should gain something
from your education.

162
00:18:03,440 --> 00:18:05,760
Insulting financial status is so…

163
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:07,440
outdated

164
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:10,040
and disgusting.

165
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:12,080
You piece of shit.

166
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:13,240
Ake!

167
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:16,280
Petch!

168
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:18,920
Petch! Ake!

169
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,800
Ake, stop!

170
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:21,880
Ake, stop!

171
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:23,720
- Such a smart mouth, huh?
- Ake!

172
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:26,040
- Ake, stop!
- Dao, let go!

173
00:18:27,640 --> 00:18:28,880
Ake!

174
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:31,320
- Petch!
- Stop!

175
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:32,600
My goodness!

176
00:18:37,480 --> 00:18:40,000
Sir, that punk.

177
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:42,320
He's trying to follow Dao.

178
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:44,280
I spoke to him nicely.

179
00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:47,720
He didn't listen and he assaulted me.

180
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:49,680
That's not true at all.

181
00:18:49,760 --> 00:18:52,760
He's lying.
He's the one who started the fight.

182
00:18:53,360 --> 00:18:55,480
Enough, Dao! Get over here!

183
00:18:57,280 --> 00:19:00,400
How could you take sides
with a man from nowhere?

184
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:01,680
Mom!

185
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:04,360
Your mother is right.

186
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:07,440
I can't believe my eyes
that you would behave like this.

187
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:09,840
We'd better talk inside later.

188
00:19:09,920 --> 00:19:12,680
For now, we should
get rid of the undesirable.

189
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:16,400
Let me be frank.

190
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:19,560
I'm forbidding you
from seeing my daughter.

191
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:22,920
Cross that line and your future is over.

192
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:29,520
Get inside, honey. Dao!

193
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:50,120
Could you please hear me out?

194
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:52,320
Petch and I didn't do anything wrong.

195
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:55,000
- Stop talking back to your parents!
- Honey.

196
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:58,480
Hitting a child is unacceptable now.

197
00:19:58,560 --> 00:20:00,440
So what else can I do?

198
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:04,200
Otherwise, we'll spoil her rotten.

199
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:07,760
Mom, I do have self-esteem.

200
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:10,040
I won't risk my future for anything.

201
00:20:10,560 --> 00:20:13,000
Could you two please trust me?

202
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:16,840
Dao, I think your parents trust you.

203
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:19,920
But I think they cannot trust that man.

204
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:22,120
To them, he's not as innocent as you are.

205
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:25,440
Yes, Ake is literally right.

206
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:28,680
You're too young.
You're no match for a man's game.

207
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:31,600
What if he talks you into something?

208
00:20:32,200 --> 00:20:37,280
Can you imagine
how ashamed we're going to be?

209
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:42,320
In the end,

210
00:20:43,520 --> 00:20:45,800
you only care about yourself.

211
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:48,160
Dao.

212
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:50,600
No more arguing.

213
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:54,480
I've made my decision
and I want you to do as I say.

214
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:58,360
You are not allowed to see Petch again.

215
00:20:58,440 --> 00:21:01,200
He cannot be your friend
or even an acquaintance.

216
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:02,240
Understood?

217
00:21:17,360 --> 00:21:21,560
FLUKE NOODLE HOUSE

218
00:21:21,640 --> 00:21:22,480
Sir.

219
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:24,840
I'll have one bowl as usual.

220
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:26,120
Petch!

221
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:30,880
Where have you been?
And why did you just get here?

222
00:21:31,840 --> 00:21:33,720
What happened to your face?

223
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:35,840
Nothing. You don't have to worry.

224
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:41,120
How's your concert staff job application?

225
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:43,160
Did they take two people?

226
00:21:44,120 --> 00:21:45,320
They took two?

227
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:46,760
Two, my ass!

228
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:48,560
I haven't submitted the application yet.

229
00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:50,840
Why?

230
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:52,360
Something happened.

231
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:53,720
- I…
- What?

232
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:55,600
I was riding my motorbike

233
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:58,760
and accidentally cut off
the car of a young miss.

234
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:04,120
By the time I figured things out with her,
the application window had closed.

235
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:05,840
Just forget it.

236
00:22:07,320 --> 00:22:08,560
Luckily, you weren't hurt.

237
00:22:09,160 --> 00:22:12,400
One more thing, Petch.
Order anything you want. My treat.

238
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:13,920
As

239
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:19,040
an apology for making you miss
the free concert.

240
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:21,520
Dam.

241
00:22:22,280 --> 00:22:24,120
What's with this big amount of money?

242
00:22:24,760 --> 00:22:29,280
The young miss in the car that hit me
gave me this consolation.

243
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:30,880
The young miss?

244
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:31,880
Wait.

245
00:22:31,960 --> 00:22:33,240
She's not a regular miss.

246
00:22:33,840 --> 00:22:34,800
She's pretty

247
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:36,600
and kind.

248
00:22:37,360 --> 00:22:38,640
I should call her…

249
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:43,640
Ms. Angel.

250
00:22:43,720 --> 00:22:45,760
Too bad you didn't meet her.

251
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:49,080
If you saw her, she's exactly your type.

252
00:22:49,680 --> 00:22:52,000
Pretty, pretty girl!

253
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:10,920
What's the matter?

254
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:12,360
Where's your phone, dear?

255
00:23:16,640 --> 00:23:17,480
Mom.

256
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:19,120
Phone is private.

257
00:23:23,600 --> 00:23:28,520
I just want to check
whether you can do as you promised.

258
00:23:30,040 --> 00:23:31,520
Such a little thing.

259
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:33,480
You won't fail us, will you?

260
00:23:54,440 --> 00:23:58,120
Such a relief that I didn't see
his name on your friend list.

261
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:04,680
Okay.

262
00:24:05,320 --> 00:24:07,240
I'm getting back to work.

263
00:24:08,320 --> 00:24:09,880
You should go to bed early.

264
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:14,280
Reading textbooks in the morning
is better for memorization.

265
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:15,760
All right?

266
00:24:15,840 --> 00:24:17,280
All right, Mom.

267
00:24:38,760 --> 00:24:40,840
PETCH PANJIN

268
00:24:50,360 --> 00:24:55,560
FLUKE NOODLE HOUSE

269
00:24:58,560 --> 00:25:01,000
NATEDAO

270
00:25:01,080 --> 00:25:04,560
LUCKILY, I ADDED YOU
FROM MY OTHER ACCOUNT.

271
00:25:04,640 --> 00:25:09,680
OR MY MOM WOULD HAVE DELETED YOU.

272
00:25:09,760 --> 00:25:13,440
DID YOUR MOM GIVE YOU A HARD TIME?

273
00:25:13,520 --> 00:25:15,080
FORGET IT, PETCH.

274
00:25:15,160 --> 00:25:19,080
I HAVE TO APOLOGIZE
ON BEHALF OF MY PARENTS.

275
00:25:19,160 --> 00:25:21,520
THEY SPOKE TO YOU BADLY.

276
00:25:22,240 --> 00:25:25,040
THAT'S ALL RIGHT.
THEY DID SO BECAUSE THEY CARE ABOUT YOU.

277
00:25:33,080 --> 00:25:33,920
Petch.

278
00:25:34,680 --> 00:25:36,200
Your noodles are getting cold.

279
00:25:37,600 --> 00:25:39,040
Okay. I know.

280
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:55,000
Petch.

281
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:58,800
You haven't touched your noodles.
Who have you been texting?

282
00:25:58,880 --> 00:26:01,880
Here we go. He's smiling at his screen.

283
00:26:04,600 --> 00:26:05,920
No, I'm not.

284
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:08,320
I'm going to see Dad.

285
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,080
I'll go with you.

286
00:26:10,160 --> 00:26:11,880
Sir. Bill, please.

287
00:26:19,480 --> 00:26:22,000
The rent and the repair are 5,000 baht.

288
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:24,520
Five thousand, boss?

289
00:26:25,040 --> 00:26:26,880
I can't afford that.

290
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:29,200
Are you trying to stiff me?

291
00:26:29,280 --> 00:26:30,560
No, I am not.

292
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:34,360
I hope you understand
that there aren't many tourists.

293
00:26:34,440 --> 00:26:36,520
Not many people order taxis these days.

294
00:26:37,120 --> 00:26:38,920
Boss, I'm begging you.

295
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:41,480
Please give me a discount on the repair.

296
00:26:41,560 --> 00:26:42,760
How dare you bargain?

297
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:45,800
If you can't pay,
go drive with someone else. Go!

298
00:26:45,880 --> 00:26:47,480
How could you do that?

299
00:26:47,560 --> 00:26:48,680
Kid!

300
00:26:48,760 --> 00:26:50,720
It's none of your business.

301
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:52,360
You're the one to blame.

302
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:53,920
You are a taxi driver.

303
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:55,560
You should've known your place.

304
00:26:55,640 --> 00:26:58,720
Wait. How is a garage owner
more special than us?

305
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:00,520
Is this how you teach your son?

306
00:27:00,600 --> 00:27:02,240
He's so rude.

307
00:27:03,320 --> 00:27:04,160
Petch.

308
00:27:05,240 --> 00:27:06,280
Stay out of it.

309
00:27:06,880 --> 00:27:08,120
You stay out of it.

310
00:27:10,160 --> 00:27:14,160
I need to talk with the selfish boss
who suppresses the inferiors.

311
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:16,000
Watch your tone!

312
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:17,720
Who suppresses your dad?

313
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:19,560
The car is yours.

314
00:27:19,640 --> 00:27:21,440
Why does my dad
have to pay for the repair?

315
00:27:22,440 --> 00:27:23,480
Are you trying to outsmart me?

316
00:27:23,560 --> 00:27:25,360
Let me be frank.

317
00:27:25,440 --> 00:27:28,400
My dad pays for the car rental every day.

318
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:30,640
That's already a heavy burden.

319
00:27:30,720 --> 00:27:33,000
But you still want
to take advantage of him?

320
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:36,360
Stop it! Stop accusing me!

321
00:27:36,440 --> 00:27:37,320
What should I say then?

322
00:27:37,400 --> 00:27:39,280
- A swindler?
- You hellhound!

323
00:27:39,360 --> 00:27:41,240
Hit him if you dare!

324
00:27:41,840 --> 00:27:44,800
That would be good evidence
for the police. Come on.

325
00:27:44,880 --> 00:27:46,200
You piece of shit!

326
00:27:46,280 --> 00:27:47,880
We can't work together!

327
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:50,480
Your dad can't work with me any longer!
Go! Leave!

328
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:51,960
Boss! Listen to me!

329
00:27:52,040 --> 00:27:52,880
I won't!

330
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:56,200
Nop, take your son back.
I'll talk to the boss.

331
00:27:56,280 --> 00:27:57,600
Boss!

332
00:28:07,920 --> 00:28:09,600
Dad!

333
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:12,680
You're doomed, Petch.

334
00:28:12,760 --> 00:28:14,360
He's so furious.

335
00:28:18,720 --> 00:28:20,040
You head back home.

336
00:28:20,920 --> 00:28:21,880
I'll talk to him.

337
00:28:27,360 --> 00:28:30,880
Thank you for doing me a favor.

338
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:34,640
I will apologize to Boss
first thing in the morning.

339
00:28:35,160 --> 00:28:36,480
I owe you this time.

340
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:41,600
You still want to work with him?

341
00:28:47,520 --> 00:28:50,880
You are not allowed
to be near my garage ever again.

342
00:28:53,880 --> 00:28:55,240
Is it so wrong

343
00:28:55,840 --> 00:28:58,040
that I hate seeing people
take advantage of you?

344
00:29:03,320 --> 00:29:04,560
If you think I was wrong,

345
00:29:05,520 --> 00:29:06,960
I apologize.

346
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:09,960
Petch.

347
00:29:10,960 --> 00:29:12,600
If being taken advantage of

348
00:29:12,680 --> 00:29:16,080
means I can have food on our table
and afford your school,

349
00:29:16,840 --> 00:29:17,720
then I accept it.

350
00:29:18,320 --> 00:29:21,280
- What?
- You're being too idealistic.

351
00:29:21,360 --> 00:29:23,240
If so, you won't survive in this society.

352
00:29:23,320 --> 00:29:25,920
That's not true.
We can't let them abuse us.

353
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:28,320
- We must stand up for ourselves.
- Quiet!

354
00:29:28,920 --> 00:29:31,080
Your one duty is to graduate!

355
00:29:31,160 --> 00:29:32,160
Nothing else!

356
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:34,760
You always make decisions for me.

357
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:37,680
- Did you say this when Mom died?
- Petch!

358
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:39,880
Mom died when I was very little.

359
00:29:41,240 --> 00:29:42,320
But I remember

360
00:29:42,840 --> 00:29:45,520
that she would support anything
I wanted to achieve.

361
00:29:46,640 --> 00:29:47,920
If she were alive,

362
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:52,600
she wouldn't draw lines
and force me like you do!

363
00:30:36,600 --> 00:30:37,440
<i>Petch.</i>

364
00:30:38,280 --> 00:30:39,240
Petch. Sweetie.

365
00:30:41,040 --> 00:30:42,360
Here's your guitar.

366
00:30:44,080 --> 00:30:45,920
Thank you, Mommy.

367
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:48,320
- I love Mommy to the moon and back.
- Sweetie.

368
00:30:49,320 --> 00:30:51,280
I love you to the moon and back.

369
00:30:56,360 --> 00:30:57,280
Great.

370
00:31:03,440 --> 00:31:05,040
Remember this, Petch.

371
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:08,160
I will always support you

372
00:31:08,760 --> 00:31:11,040
in anything you love.

373
00:31:12,520 --> 00:31:14,880
As long as you try your best.

374
00:31:49,080 --> 00:31:54,840
NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS,
MUSIC CAN HEAL ALL WOUNDS.

375
00:31:58,600 --> 00:32:00,600
NATEDAO

376
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:28,760
AIR-CONDITIONED BUS, 10 BAHT

377
00:33:33,320 --> 00:33:35,360
FIRST TIME ON THE BUS.

378
00:33:48,880 --> 00:33:49,760
Here.

379
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:52,160
The Rock Concert tickets.

380
00:33:52,240 --> 00:33:53,160
- Rock on!
- Joe.

381
00:33:53,240 --> 00:33:55,680
- They're sold out.
- Are you giving it to us for free?

382
00:33:55,760 --> 00:33:58,280
We're going to the concert!

383
00:33:58,360 --> 00:33:59,200
So cool!

384
00:33:59,920 --> 00:34:00,920
- Let's go!
- Hey!

385
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:02,160
Not for free.

386
00:34:02,240 --> 00:34:03,640
I want you to sell them.

387
00:34:05,800 --> 00:34:06,880
- Sell them?
- Sell them?

388
00:34:06,960 --> 00:34:07,960
Yes.

389
00:34:08,040 --> 00:34:09,800
So that I can clear my debt.

390
00:34:10,719 --> 00:34:11,840
Sell them for extra.

391
00:34:11,920 --> 00:34:13,360
Plus 500 each.

392
00:34:15,600 --> 00:34:16,960
Sell them all!

393
00:34:18,880 --> 00:34:19,800
Okay, bro.

394
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:23,080
- We have The Rock Concert tickets.
- This way.

395
00:34:23,159 --> 00:34:24,639
- Rock on.
- Real tickets.

396
00:34:24,719 --> 00:34:27,719
- We have The Rock Concert tickets.
- This way.

397
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:28,760
Guys.

398
00:34:29,360 --> 00:34:31,199
You have The Rock Concert tickets?

399
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:33,360
Are these real?

400
00:34:33,440 --> 00:34:35,320
- Careful.
- Watch it.

401
00:34:35,400 --> 00:34:36,639
These are real!

402
00:34:37,239 --> 00:34:38,159
Want to buy some?

403
00:34:38,760 --> 00:34:40,080
Can you afford it?

404
00:34:40,159 --> 00:34:41,360
How much?

405
00:34:42,199 --> 00:34:43,120
One thousand each.

406
00:34:44,920 --> 00:34:47,639
One thousand? That price is too much!

407
00:34:47,719 --> 00:34:49,480
Are you out of your mind?

408
00:34:49,560 --> 00:34:50,600
Dam.

409
00:34:51,520 --> 00:34:53,320
Just admit that you can't afford it.

410
00:34:54,159 --> 00:34:55,440
I can give you a discount.

411
00:34:57,040 --> 00:34:57,920
How much?

412
00:34:59,560 --> 00:35:01,040
Special price for you,

413
00:35:01,560 --> 00:35:02,400
dog.

414
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:05,760
Two thousand each.

415
00:35:06,920 --> 00:35:07,920
This can't be.

416
00:35:08,440 --> 00:35:09,720
Are you out of your mind?

417
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:11,720
This is robbery.

418
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:14,600
Fine. Many people want them anyway.

419
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:16,280
Let's go.

420
00:35:16,360 --> 00:35:18,520
Wait. I'll take it.

421
00:35:26,280 --> 00:35:27,600
Come on.

422
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:29,400
I know.

423
00:35:37,040 --> 00:35:39,120
Thank you, customer.

424
00:35:39,960 --> 00:35:40,960
Let's get going.

425
00:35:41,560 --> 00:35:44,760
We've made 2,000
from The Rock Concert tickets.

426
00:35:45,280 --> 00:35:48,040
The Rock Concert tickets here!

427
00:35:54,640 --> 00:35:55,480
Petch.

428
00:35:56,360 --> 00:35:57,560
What's up?

429
00:35:59,280 --> 00:36:00,360
What?

430
00:36:01,400 --> 00:36:04,160
The authentic The Rock Concert ticket!

431
00:36:05,080 --> 00:36:06,240
Where did you get this?

432
00:36:07,200 --> 00:36:08,720
Just forget it.

433
00:36:12,000 --> 00:36:13,800
Are we really going to the concert?

434
00:36:14,400 --> 00:36:15,400
When is it?

435
00:36:16,040 --> 00:36:17,720
Tomorrow, 8:00 p.m.

436
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:20,800
Without me. Don't be late.

437
00:36:23,040 --> 00:36:24,480
What?

438
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:26,720
You talk like you won't come with me.

439
00:36:27,920 --> 00:36:30,400
Right. There's one ticket.

440
00:36:35,400 --> 00:36:36,560
Take it back then.

441
00:36:36,640 --> 00:36:38,600
Hey. No.

442
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:40,120
You are the guitarist.

443
00:36:40,200 --> 00:36:41,920
You must see this show.

444
00:36:43,960 --> 00:36:45,880
Tomorrow, I can't go anywhere.

445
00:36:45,960 --> 00:36:46,920
Why?

446
00:36:49,080 --> 00:36:50,720
My dad won't be working tomorrow.

447
00:36:50,800 --> 00:36:52,920
He won't let me go to the concert.

448
00:36:55,400 --> 00:36:58,600
But this concert is only held once a year.

449
00:36:58,680 --> 00:36:59,720
You can't miss it.

450
00:36:59,800 --> 00:37:00,680
But--

451
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:02,000
About your dad,

452
00:37:02,800 --> 00:37:03,880
I'll take care of it.

453
00:37:24,440 --> 00:37:25,880
Littering like a little kid.

454
00:37:26,480 --> 00:37:27,960
Eating uncooked instant noodles.

455
00:37:48,560 --> 00:37:50,720
Noodles are ready, honey.

456
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:51,800
Okay.

457
00:37:51,880 --> 00:37:52,960
He's asleep.

458
00:37:54,080 --> 00:37:55,840
He's so easy to take care of.

459
00:37:58,240 --> 00:38:00,720
Have the noodles, honey.
The soup is still hot.

460
00:38:01,440 --> 00:38:02,600
What about you?

461
00:38:02,680 --> 00:38:05,760
I only bought one pack.

462
00:38:05,840 --> 00:38:07,200
Go ahead. It's okay.

463
00:38:08,240 --> 00:38:10,080
Well, I think

464
00:38:10,800 --> 00:38:11,920
you should have it.

465
00:38:13,520 --> 00:38:16,040
Let's eat it together then.

466
00:38:20,720 --> 00:38:21,680
I'm sorry, honey.

467
00:38:23,040 --> 00:38:25,320
I never took you to any fancy restaurants.

468
00:38:26,040 --> 00:38:27,880
That's totally fine.

469
00:38:27,960 --> 00:38:29,520
I'll tell you what.

470
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:32,680
This bowl of noodles
is much tastier than fancy dishes.

471
00:38:32,760 --> 00:38:33,960
Really?

472
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:35,120
Yes.

473
00:38:35,200 --> 00:38:40,440
For me, the taste is not about the place,

474
00:38:40,520 --> 00:38:43,440
but it's about the person
we share it with.

475
00:38:45,560 --> 00:38:46,480
Let's eat.

476
00:38:48,040 --> 00:38:49,600
Here you go.

477
00:38:49,680 --> 00:38:50,840
Thank you, honey.

478
00:39:16,480 --> 00:39:18,160
- Hello?
- Petch.

479
00:39:20,080 --> 00:39:22,720
I forgot I have to be quiet.
How are you over there?

480
00:39:22,800 --> 00:39:24,960
I'm in the queue to get inside the hall.

481
00:39:25,040 --> 00:39:27,800
Rock on, bro.

482
00:39:29,160 --> 00:39:30,120
How's my dad doing?

483
00:39:31,640 --> 00:39:33,240
He's probably downstairs.

484
00:39:33,320 --> 00:39:34,720
Petch!

485
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:36,720
Petch, I need to hang up.

486
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:37,800
Later, man.

487
00:39:41,760 --> 00:39:42,800
Petch.

488
00:39:43,320 --> 00:39:44,480
What are you doing?

489
00:39:45,080 --> 00:39:46,600
Why don't you have your dinner?

490
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:50,640
<i>I'm reading my textbook.</i>

491
00:39:50,720 --> 00:39:52,040
Oh, wow.

492
00:39:52,120 --> 00:39:54,960
Reading without me reminding you.

493
00:39:55,040 --> 00:39:55,880
Fine.

494
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:58,280
I'll put dinner in the fridge.

495
00:39:58,360 --> 00:40:01,080
Heat it up when you're hungry.

496
00:40:04,040 --> 00:40:05,000
<i>Thank you.</i>

497
00:40:05,080 --> 00:40:07,760
Okay. I won't bother you.

498
00:40:08,440 --> 00:40:10,000
Read it mindfully, son.

499
00:40:12,160 --> 00:40:13,440
My son is studying hard.

500
00:40:23,560 --> 00:40:24,400
Wait.

501
00:40:25,120 --> 00:40:29,080
Check the lights,
the sound, and the artists' cues.

502
00:40:29,160 --> 00:40:30,240
It must be flawless.

503
00:40:31,280 --> 00:40:34,240
Ake is talented.
He's the concert producer.

504
00:40:34,320 --> 00:40:38,080
He also invited us two for free.

505
00:40:38,160 --> 00:40:39,000
Yes.

506
00:40:39,080 --> 00:40:40,480
You are so lucky.

507
00:40:40,560 --> 00:40:42,760
Your boyfriend
is both talented and handsome.

508
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:45,840
No, Ake is not my boyfriend.

509
00:40:45,920 --> 00:40:46,960
He won't be.

510
00:40:47,560 --> 00:40:50,760
If you don't like Ake,
who do you have in mind?

511
00:40:50,840 --> 00:40:51,760
Right.

512
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:56,200
Ladies.

513
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:58,000
What are you gossiping about?

514
00:40:58,080 --> 00:40:59,320
The show will start soon.

515
00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:01,160
Ake.

516
00:41:01,680 --> 00:41:03,680
Pin and Prae want to see Ohm.

517
00:41:04,200 --> 00:41:05,200
Right.

518
00:41:05,280 --> 00:41:08,160
We want to give Ohm this bouquet.
Please take us to him.

519
00:41:08,240 --> 00:41:10,080
All right. No biggie.

520
00:41:10,160 --> 00:41:11,960
- Yes!
- Ake, you are the kindest man!

521
00:41:12,480 --> 00:41:13,360
Come on, Dao.

522
00:41:14,160 --> 00:41:16,280
It's all right. I'll wait here.

523
00:41:17,320 --> 00:41:19,280
Please take care of my friends.

524
00:41:20,160 --> 00:41:23,000
All right. Wait here, Dao.

525
00:41:23,080 --> 00:41:24,080
I'll be right back.

526
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:27,400
- Let's go.
- This way, ladies.

527
00:42:05,760 --> 00:42:11,040
PETCH PANJIN

528
00:42:17,240 --> 00:42:18,400
Petch is here?

529
00:42:56,160 --> 00:42:57,120
He doesn't pick up.

530
00:43:01,160 --> 00:43:03,000
<i>Gazing at the sky</i>

531
00:43:04,040 --> 00:43:06,840
<i>Wishing for a brighter day</i>

532
00:43:06,920 --> 00:43:10,800
<i>Let the memories of the past</i>
<i>Simply fade away</i>

533
00:43:10,880 --> 00:43:14,320
<i>Today is brand new</i>

534
00:43:14,400 --> 00:43:16,400
<i>And as the sun</i>

535
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,240
<i>Breaks through the rain</i>

536
00:43:20,760 --> 00:43:23,960
<i>A rainbow weaves its colors</i>
<i>To chase the dark away</i>

537
00:43:24,040 --> 00:43:25,920
<i>With clarity in my eyes</i>

538
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:30,400
<i>I finally find my way</i>

539
00:43:30,480 --> 00:43:33,280
<i>Before exhaustion takes its toll</i>

540
00:43:33,360 --> 00:43:37,320
<i>Before time slips beyond control</i>

541
00:43:37,400 --> 00:43:41,160
<i>I've learned that when I stop searching</i>

542
00:43:41,240 --> 00:43:44,680
<i>Everything finds its place</i>

543
00:43:59,000 --> 00:44:01,200
<i>When reality is not</i>

544
00:44:02,280 --> 00:44:04,680
<i>What meets the eye</i>

545
00:44:05,520 --> 00:44:08,800
<i>Joy and pain are real</i>
<i>And truth can never lie</i>

546
00:44:08,880 --> 00:44:12,680
<i>That is the answer to find</i>

547
